  <fishName>k__BackingField: Hammerhead Shark
  <fishFact>k__BackingField: "That wide, flat head isn't just strange-looking \u2014
    it's a superpower. The hammerhead's eyes are positioned on each end, giving it
    nearly 360-degree vision, and the broad surface is packed with electroreceptors
    so sensitive they can detect the faint electrical field of a heartbeat hidden
    under sand. They also commonly school in large groups during the day, which is
    unusual behavior for sharks. "
